1
00:00:00,792 --> 00:00:03,628
<i>We're still looking for the people</i>
<i>who took the money from the drop-off.</i>

2
00:00:03,712 --> 00:00:05,046
<i>All ours!</i>

3
00:00:05,130 --> 00:00:06,631
<i>They can't hurt me anymore!</i>

4
00:00:06,715 --> 00:00:09,259
<i>No one will hurt you again!</i>
[LAUGHING]

5
00:00:09,342 --> 00:00:11,219
<i>Did you see that? That one's crazy.</i>

6
00:00:11,302 --> 00:00:14,097
<i>What happened to Uno? Is he okay?</i>

7
00:00:14,180 --> 00:00:16,391
<i>There was a call from</i>
<i>the San Marcelino PD in Cavite.</i>

8
00:00:16,474 --> 00:00:18,852
<i>A kidnapping report from La Playa Roja.</i>

9
00:00:18,935 --> 00:00:20,687
<i>A call got through.</i>

10
00:00:20,770 --> 00:00:22,063
<i>Did he give a name?</i>

11
00:00:22,147 --> 00:00:24,691
<i>- Who made the call?</i>
<i>- Liam Roja.</i>

12
00:00:24,774 --> 00:00:27,736
[OLSEN] <i>The cops you called are</i>
<i>in cahoots with them, Liam.</i>

13
00:00:27,819 --> 00:00:31,072
[LUNA] <i>So that means no help is coming?</i>

14
00:00:31,156 --> 00:00:32,866
<i>Take these two out of here!</i>

15
00:00:33,283 --> 00:00:35,326
- [GROANS] <i>What do you want?!</i>
<i>- Don't hurt us!</i>

16
00:00:35,410 --> 00:00:38,079
<i>Try to call for help. I'll go after Mama.</i>

17
00:00:38,163 --> 00:00:40,165
- [LUNA] <i>Liam, are you sure?</i>
<i>- Take care.</i>

18
00:00:40,623 --> 00:00:41,541
[LIAM] <i>Take care.</i>

19
00:00:41,624 --> 00:00:43,334
[EMIL] <i>Liam Roja!</i>

20
00:00:43,418 --> 00:00:45,545
<i>We know you're here on the island.</i>

21
00:00:45,628 --> 00:00:46,838
<i>I'll count to ten.</i>

22
00:00:46,921 --> 00:00:50,592
<i>If you don't show up by then,</i>
<i>I will kill your parents.</i>

23
00:00:50,675 --> 00:00:51,509
[EMIL] <i>One!</i>

24
00:00:53,845 --> 00:00:55,388
[SOFT SOB]

25
00:00:56,347 --> 00:00:58,308
[EMIL] <i>Will you let them die, Liam?!</i>

26
00:00:58,850 --> 00:01:00,560
- <i>Nine!</i>
- [SCREAMS] No!

27
00:01:02,062 --> 00:01:03,229
<i>- Liam!</i>
- [MAN] <i>Shut up.</i>

28
00:01:06,357 --> 00:01:08,610
- [TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]
- We're almost there, Luna.

29
00:01:08,693 --> 00:01:11,863
I have to go back to Liam.
He needs my help.

30
00:01:11,946 --> 00:01:13,907
- Luna! Luna! Luna!
- [TENSE MUSIC RISES]

31
00:01:13,990 --> 00:01:15,241
Luna, wait!

32
00:01:17,368 --> 00:01:20,246
- [MUSIC FADES]
- [WATER SPLASHING]

33
00:01:22,123 --> 00:01:23,917
[GOON, MAGNUS GRUNT]

34
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:26,503
- Stay there!
- [GOON, MAGNUS GRUNT]

35
00:01:26,586 --> 00:01:28,421
- [GRETA GROANS]
- Liam!

36
00:01:28,505 --> 00:01:29,631
[GRETA GROANS]

37
00:01:30,882 --> 00:01:32,717
[EMIL] You're good, kid.

38
00:01:34,594 --> 00:01:37,096
How were you able to call the police?

39
00:01:37,180 --> 00:01:38,556
Huh?

40
00:01:38,640 --> 00:01:43,603
[LOW, SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

41
00:01:44,062 --> 00:01:46,314
[EMIL] Tell me,

42
00:01:46,397 --> 00:01:48,733
where are your companions

43
00:01:48,817 --> 00:01:51,194
and the other resort guests hiding?

44
00:01:51,903 --> 00:01:54,656
I don't know what companions
you're talking about.

45
00:01:55,115 --> 00:01:56,241
[EMIL SCOFFS]

46
00:01:56,324 --> 00:01:57,742
You don't know?

47
00:01:59,202 --> 00:02:00,995
Olsen Bonifacio,

48
00:02:01,496 --> 00:02:03,206
Ben Bonifacio,

49
00:02:03,289 --> 00:02:04,791
and Luna Javier?

50
00:02:05,667 --> 00:02:07,418
And the other guests?

51
00:02:07,919 --> 00:02:09,796
I know

52
00:02:09,879 --> 00:02:12,173
you know where they are hiding.

53
00:02:12,757 --> 00:02:13,842
Huh?

54
00:02:13,925 --> 00:02:17,053
- Tell me!
- I don't know what you mean!

55
00:02:18,805 --> 00:02:20,557
[EMIL] You don't know, huh?

56
00:02:21,015 --> 00:02:22,350
You won't tell me?

57
00:02:23,643 --> 00:02:24,894
Get him up.

58
00:02:24,978 --> 00:02:26,563
Hey. Hey! Hey!

59
00:02:26,646 --> 00:02:29,315
- Let go of me!
- [LIAM GRUNTING]

60
00:02:29,774 --> 00:02:31,401
- [BLOW LANDS]
- Argh!

61
00:02:31,484 --> 00:02:33,278
[GRETA WHIMPERS]

62
00:02:33,361 --> 00:02:35,321
[EMIL] What?!

63
00:02:35,405 --> 00:02:39,117
- Tell me!
- [MAGNUS COUGHS, GROANS]

64
00:02:39,200 --> 00:02:40,785
[COUGHS]

65
00:02:40,869 --> 00:02:42,287
[EMIL] You really won't tell me?

66
00:02:42,871 --> 00:02:44,372
- Get him up.
- [MAGNUS GROANS]

67
00:02:44,455 --> 00:02:45,957
[GRUNTING ANGRILY] Let me go!

68
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:48,877
- [BLOW LANDS]
- [MAGNUS YELLS IN PAIN]

69
00:02:48,960 --> 00:02:53,590
[GRUNTS, COUGHS]

70
00:02:53,673 --> 00:02:54,924
[EMIL] Where are they?!

71
00:02:55,008 --> 00:02:56,509
[MAGNUS GROANS]

72
00:02:57,093 --> 00:02:59,637
[EMIL] Do you really not care
about your dad?

73
00:02:59,721 --> 00:03:06,019
You'll let him die just to save people
who aren't even your family?

74
00:03:07,812 --> 00:03:09,022
Put a cover on this head.

75
00:03:09,898 --> 00:03:12,483
- Hey! Wait a minute! Hey!
- [GRETA CRIES]

76
00:03:12,567 --> 00:03:15,486
- Stop this, please!
- [EMIL] So?! Where are they?

77
00:03:15,570 --> 00:03:17,155
- [MAGNUS GASPS]
- [GRETA] Stop it. Magnus…

78
00:03:17,238 --> 00:03:18,865
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

79
00:03:18,948 --> 00:03:22,952
If it doesn't work with the dad,
do it on the mom!

80
00:03:23,036 --> 00:03:24,203
Go!

81
00:03:24,287 --> 00:03:26,706
- [WHIMPERS]
- No! Let go of her! Stop!

82
00:03:26,789 --> 00:03:28,041
Stop it!

83
00:03:29,417 --> 00:03:34,213
[GASPING FOR AIR]

84
00:03:34,297 --> 00:03:37,342
[GRETA CRYING]

85
00:03:37,425 --> 00:03:40,637
- [BREATHING HEAVILY]
- [MUSIC TURNS LOW, TENSE]

86
00:03:40,720 --> 00:03:44,098
[GRETA WHIMPERS, BREATHES HEAVILY]

87
00:03:44,182 --> 00:03:46,976
[EMIL] Where are they, Liam?

88
00:03:47,060 --> 00:03:48,811
[MUSIC FADES]

89
00:03:49,938 --> 00:03:52,482
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC RISES]

90
00:04:00,573 --> 00:04:07,580
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

91
00:04:25,807 --> 00:04:27,976
Papa, why aren't they here yet?

92
00:04:28,059 --> 00:04:30,478
I'm worried they could be in danger.

93
00:04:30,561 --> 00:04:33,314
We have no idea what's happening.

94
00:04:33,398 --> 00:04:37,193
You said help's coming, right?

95
00:04:37,277 --> 00:04:39,654
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

96
00:04:39,737 --> 00:04:41,614
Uh… Yes, Maddie.

97
00:04:41,698 --> 00:04:47,453
You'll be with your mom
and dad very soon, okay?

98
00:04:47,537 --> 00:04:49,330
Papa.

99
00:04:49,414 --> 00:04:52,208
What's going on outside?

100
00:04:52,292 --> 00:04:55,712
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

101
00:04:55,795 --> 00:04:59,507
[YOUNG OLSEN] <i>Did the doctor</i>
<i>say I can finally go home?</i>

102
00:05:01,175 --> 00:05:04,637
[VOICE BREAKING]
<i>Yes, you're all better now, son.</i>

103
00:05:04,721 --> 00:05:05,888
[WENDY SNIFFLES]

104
00:05:08,016 --> 00:05:09,934
- [SNIFFLES]
- [SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

105
00:05:10,018 --> 00:05:11,519
<i>They're here, dear.</i>

106
00:05:12,353 --> 00:05:14,856
<i>You be a good boy, okay?</i>

107
00:05:14,939 --> 00:05:19,027
<i>Always obey your grandpa.</i>

108
00:05:19,110 --> 00:05:21,612
<i>- Okay?</i>
- [YOUNG OLSEN]<i> Where are you going?</i>

109
00:05:21,696 --> 00:05:23,865
[WENDY] <i>Always remember</i>
<i>that I love you so much.</i>

110
00:05:23,948 --> 00:05:25,241
[WENDY SNIFFLES, SOBS SOFTLY]

111
00:05:25,325 --> 00:05:27,952
[YOUNG OLSEN] <i>Ma? Ma!</i>

112
00:05:28,578 --> 00:05:32,457
<i>Wendy Bonifacio, you're under</i>
<i>arrest for syndicated estafa.</i>

113
00:05:32,540 --> 00:05:34,542
<i>You have the right to remain silent.</i>

114
00:05:34,625 --> 00:05:38,254
<i>Anything you say can and will</i>
<i>be used against you in court.</i>

115
00:05:38,337 --> 00:05:39,797
- [HURRIED FOOTSTEPS]
- [WENDY SOBBING]

116
00:05:39,881 --> 00:05:44,052
[SOBBING] <i>Ma! What are they doing to you?!</i>

117
00:05:44,135 --> 00:05:47,555
<i>Why are they putting you in handcuffs?!</i>

118
00:05:47,638 --> 00:05:49,724
<i>Papa…</i>

119
00:05:49,807 --> 00:05:52,060
[VOICE CRACKING]
<i>Please take care of Olsen.</i>

120
00:05:52,143 --> 00:05:57,940
- [SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [BOTH SOBBING]

121
00:05:58,024 --> 00:06:02,070
<i>Ma! Don't leave me!</i>

122
00:06:02,153 --> 00:06:03,279
[SNIFFLES]

123
00:06:03,362 --> 00:06:05,239
<i>I'm sorry, son.</i>

124
00:06:05,323 --> 00:06:07,075
<i>Ma!</i>

125
00:06:07,158 --> 00:06:10,036
[SOBBING] <i>Don't leave me, Ma!</i>

126
00:06:11,079 --> 00:06:12,872
[YOUNG OLSEN SCREAMS] <i>Ma!</i>

127
00:06:14,248 --> 00:06:19,170
There's no pain greater for a parent
than being apart from their child.

128
00:06:19,253 --> 00:06:22,924
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

129
00:06:23,007 --> 00:06:25,676
I went through that with Olsen, Papa.

130
00:06:29,764 --> 00:06:34,060
That's why I'm sure that
wherever Maddie's parents are…

131
00:06:36,145 --> 00:06:39,148
they carry that same pain.

132
00:06:39,232 --> 00:06:41,484
[MUSIC FADES]

133
00:06:44,278 --> 00:06:45,905
[FIN] Bro!

134
00:06:45,988 --> 00:06:50,493
- [TENSE MUSIC PLAYS]
- Olsen! Son! What happened?!

135
00:06:50,576 --> 00:06:53,496
We heard them calling Liam
over the PA system.

136
00:06:53,579 --> 00:06:57,583
- Where is he?
- They took her to the poolside.

137
00:06:57,667 --> 00:06:59,752
That's why Liam went off on his own.

138
00:06:59,836 --> 00:07:02,130
- Luna followed him.
- What?

139
00:07:02,213 --> 00:07:04,048
Why were Liam's parents
taken to the poolside?

140
00:07:05,508 --> 00:07:09,470
But help is coming, right? It's coming?

141
00:07:09,554 --> 00:07:11,055
- I don't think help's coming.
- [MAMA ONA] Huh?

142
00:07:11,139 --> 00:07:14,851
The cops Liam called are on their side.

143
00:07:14,934 --> 00:07:18,229
Oh my God, no! Wait! So no
one's gonna rescue us?!

144
00:07:18,312 --> 00:07:19,564
- What will we do?!
- Calm down.

145
00:07:19,647 --> 00:07:22,108
- Let's try calling again.
- You're scaring the kid.

146
00:07:22,191 --> 00:07:24,318
Chief Ben, let's fix that thing.

147
00:07:24,402 --> 00:07:26,821
- Grandpa, help me get a signal.
- All right, let me see.

148
00:07:26,904 --> 00:07:28,239
- [SHUSHES]
- [MAMA ONA WHIMPERS]

149
00:07:28,322 --> 00:07:29,699
[BEN] I'll hold this up.

150
00:07:29,782 --> 00:07:33,619
- [PANICKED BREATHS]
- [TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

151
00:07:33,703 --> 00:07:35,872
Is there a signal yet?

152
00:07:35,955 --> 00:07:38,541
- [TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [PANICKED BREATHS]

153
00:07:38,624 --> 00:07:40,543
[FIN] Still no signal, bro?

154
00:07:40,626 --> 00:07:43,296
- [TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]
- No, bro.

155
00:07:43,379 --> 00:07:45,465
- Why is there no signal?
- Wait, just calm down.

156
00:07:45,548 --> 00:07:47,216
- [BEN] Just keep trying.
- Yes, I'm trying.

157
00:07:47,300 --> 00:07:49,177
- Oh my gosh.
- [BEN] I'll hold it up higher.

158
00:07:50,887 --> 00:07:55,016
How much longer? My arms are killing me!

159
00:07:55,099 --> 00:07:56,100
[PHONE THUDS]

160
00:07:56,184 --> 00:07:57,477
[MAMA ONA WHIMPERS]

161
00:07:57,560 --> 00:08:00,313
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES, TRAILS OFF]

162
00:08:06,736 --> 00:08:08,738
[TENSE STING]

163
00:08:13,409 --> 00:08:15,203
- [GOON] Gotcha!
- [SUSPENSEFUL STING]

164
00:08:15,286 --> 00:08:20,291
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

165
00:08:20,374 --> 00:08:21,834
[BOTH GRUNT]

166
00:08:21,918 --> 00:08:23,961
- [BLOW LANDS]
- [LUNA GRUNTS]

167
00:08:24,045 --> 00:08:25,463
- [BLOW LANDS]
- [BOTH GRUNT]

168
00:08:25,546 --> 00:08:27,256
- [GOON THUDS]
- [SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC RISES]

169
00:08:27,340 --> 00:08:29,842
- [GUN CLATTERS]
- [TENSE STING]

170
00:08:31,928 --> 00:08:34,222
- [KNIFE WHOOSHES]
- [LUNA GRUNTS]

171
00:08:34,305 --> 00:08:35,515
[GWEN GRUNTS]

172
00:08:38,309 --> 00:08:40,478
- [KICK LANDS]
- [KNIFE CLATTERS]

173
00:08:40,561 --> 00:08:41,687
[EXHALES HEAVILY]

174
00:08:41,771 --> 00:08:47,151
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

175
00:08:47,235 --> 00:08:48,986
- [BOTH GRUNT]
- [BLOW LANDS]

176
00:08:49,070 --> 00:08:51,822
- [LUNA GRUNTS]
- [BLOW LANDS]

177
00:08:51,906 --> 00:08:53,115
[THUDS]

178
00:08:53,199 --> 00:08:55,618
[TENSE MUSIC BUILDS]

179
00:08:55,701 --> 00:08:59,163
[GWEN] Ah… You never learn, don't you?

180
00:08:59,247 --> 00:09:03,251
- You think you can beat me.
- [LUNA PANTS]

181
00:09:03,334 --> 00:09:04,794
[TENSE MUSIC BUILDS, FADES]

182
00:09:04,877 --> 00:09:05,920
[BEN] So?

183
00:09:06,003 --> 00:09:07,922
[OLSEN PANTING]

184
00:09:08,005 --> 00:09:09,966
[BEN] Any signal yet?

185
00:09:10,049 --> 00:09:11,551
[OLSEN] No, Grandpa.

186
00:09:11,634 --> 00:09:13,135
[DOOR OPENS]

187
00:09:13,219 --> 00:09:16,389
- [GOON] Hey!
- [SCREAMS, WHIMPERS]

188
00:09:16,472 --> 00:09:18,849
- [WENDY] Pa!
- [TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

189
00:09:18,933 --> 00:09:21,227
Where's the gun, Fin?

190
00:09:21,310 --> 00:09:23,688
- Fin?
- It's too--It's too far.

191
00:09:23,771 --> 00:09:24,605
I can't reach it.

192
00:09:24,689 --> 00:09:26,691
- [GOON 1] Move back!
- [GOON 2] I'll shoot you.

193
00:09:28,276 --> 00:09:31,153
[MAMA ONA SQUEALS IN FRIGHT]

194
00:09:31,237 --> 00:09:32,405
[WHIMPERS]

195
00:09:32,488 --> 00:09:34,073
[GOON 2] Don't move! Give me the gun!

196
00:09:34,156 --> 00:09:35,866
- [BEN] Olsen.
- Damn it.

197
00:09:35,950 --> 00:09:42,748
[TENSE MUSIC RISING]

198
00:09:45,001 --> 00:09:46,627
[WENDY] Pa…

199
00:09:46,711 --> 00:09:49,880
- [GOON] Move it!
- Yes! I'm going, I'm going!

200
00:09:49,964 --> 00:09:51,549
[WENDY BREATHES HEAVILY]

201
00:09:51,632 --> 00:09:53,968
Son… Son…

202
00:09:54,051 --> 00:09:55,595
[GOON 1] Move away!

203
00:09:55,678 --> 00:09:56,929
[GOON 3] Stand there!

204
00:09:59,348 --> 00:10:04,353
- [WHIMPERING, SHRIEKING]
- [OBJECTS CLATTER]

205
00:10:04,437 --> 00:10:06,188
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

206
00:10:06,272 --> 00:10:07,273
Damn it.

207
00:10:10,860 --> 00:10:12,486
[MUSIC FADES]

208
00:10:12,570 --> 00:10:14,905
Investigate the robbery in Orosa.

209
00:10:14,989 --> 00:10:16,782
Report to me tomorrow.

210
00:10:16,866 --> 00:10:17,992
- Yes, sir.
- Okay.

211
00:10:19,160 --> 00:10:23,372
[FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING]

212
00:10:24,206 --> 00:10:26,042
Good afternoon, Major Domingo.

213
00:10:28,085 --> 00:10:32,757
I was told about the incident
at La Playa Roja.

214
00:10:32,840 --> 00:10:35,635
Oh, it's not an incident, sir.

215
00:10:35,718 --> 00:10:37,637
Looks like a prank call.

216
00:10:37,720 --> 00:10:41,807
Someone pretended to be the son
of the owner of La Playa Roja.

217
00:10:41,891 --> 00:10:45,561
Who reported that there was
a hostage situation?

218
00:10:45,645 --> 00:10:48,272
Yes, sir. But we already
traced the number.

219
00:10:49,023 --> 00:10:50,941
We can file charges
against the prank caller.

220
00:10:51,025 --> 00:10:53,819
But there was an incident
in San Martin, right?

221
00:10:53,903 --> 00:10:55,988
A kidnap-for-ransom.

222
00:10:56,822 --> 00:11:00,242
And the victims were from La Playa Roja.

223
00:11:01,202 --> 00:11:03,329
It's an isolated case, sir.

224
00:11:03,412 --> 00:11:07,208
We just need to make sure
there's no anomaly happening.

225
00:11:07,291 --> 00:11:10,795
I want you to send a team out
to La Playa Roja.

226
00:11:10,878 --> 00:11:11,879
Understood?

227
00:11:12,671 --> 00:11:14,048
Can I volunteer, sir?

228
00:11:15,800 --> 00:11:17,093
Thank you, sir.

229
00:11:17,176 --> 00:11:18,969
Copy, sir.

230
00:11:19,053 --> 00:11:21,472
I will coordinate with the Coast Guard.

231
00:11:22,973 --> 00:11:24,266
Captain Jacinto…

232
00:11:25,726 --> 00:11:26,936
This is urgent.

233
00:11:28,354 --> 00:11:31,565
I want you to assign
our best man to this case.

234
00:11:31,649 --> 00:11:32,775
You understand?

235
00:11:34,068 --> 00:11:35,611
Assign Areza.

236
00:11:37,696 --> 00:11:38,823
Copy, sir.

237
00:11:41,659 --> 00:11:45,079
[FOREBODING MUSIC CONTINUES]

238
00:11:45,162 --> 00:11:46,163
Go on.

239
00:11:51,836 --> 00:11:54,213
Uno, Liam Roja's tip was right.

240
00:11:54,296 --> 00:11:57,591
His companions are in the mechanical room.

241
00:11:57,675 --> 00:11:58,759
Good.

242
00:11:59,635 --> 00:12:01,345
<i>None of those people is important.</i>

243
00:12:01,429 --> 00:12:03,055
What, sir?

244
00:12:03,139 --> 00:12:04,849
Take them all down.

245
00:12:05,683 --> 00:12:07,810
- [WENDY CRYING]
- You heard that, Grandpa?

246
00:12:07,893 --> 00:12:08,769
Calm down.

247
00:12:08,853 --> 00:12:10,438
Grandpa, did you hear that?!

248
00:12:10,521 --> 00:12:11,814
[BEN] Calm down.

249
00:12:11,897 --> 00:12:16,152
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

250
00:12:28,414 --> 00:12:29,623
Thank you, Liam.

251
00:12:30,708 --> 00:12:32,418
You made my job easier.

252
00:12:33,669 --> 00:12:35,921
Do you have any last words for them?

253
00:12:39,300 --> 00:12:40,718
- You monster!
- Liam!

254
00:12:42,136 --> 00:12:44,472
You betrayed your friends.

255
00:12:45,723 --> 00:12:47,850
Doesn't that make you the monster?

256
00:12:47,933 --> 00:12:49,143
- [BLOW LANDS]
- Son!

257
00:12:50,686 --> 00:12:54,899
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

258
00:12:54,982 --> 00:12:55,941
What now?

259
00:12:57,318 --> 00:12:58,986
You've seen my face.

260
00:13:01,405 --> 00:13:03,282
All of you have.

261
00:13:03,365 --> 00:13:04,492
[GRETA] We won't tell anyone.

262
00:13:04,575 --> 00:13:05,993
We don't even know who you are.

263
00:13:07,036 --> 00:13:09,038
- Really?
- [GRETA WHIMPERS]

264
00:13:09,121 --> 00:13:10,206
Huh?

265
00:13:10,289 --> 00:13:12,625
[MAGNUS] I told you we would pay
whatever the amount.

266
00:13:12,708 --> 00:13:15,503
A hundred million, two hundred million.

267
00:13:15,586 --> 00:13:17,963
Please have mercy on my family.

268
00:13:18,047 --> 00:13:20,007
You're a great father.

269
00:13:21,717 --> 00:13:23,219
But a great husband?

270
00:13:24,512 --> 00:13:25,346
I don't think so.

271
00:13:25,429 --> 00:13:30,100
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

272
00:13:30,184 --> 00:13:31,644
We'll pay more for the others too.

273
00:13:31,727 --> 00:13:33,521
For the ones I want dead?

274
00:13:33,604 --> 00:13:35,356
They have nothing to do with this!

275
00:13:35,439 --> 00:13:37,274
They do!

276
00:13:37,358 --> 00:13:39,068
They escaped with you.

277
00:13:39,902 --> 00:13:41,820
For me, that's unacceptable.

278
00:13:44,490 --> 00:13:45,533
Sometimes,

279
00:13:46,700 --> 00:13:48,994
people need to be taught a lesson.

280
00:13:50,746 --> 00:13:57,753
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

281
00:14:00,381 --> 00:14:02,383
[LIAM] Please kill me instead!

282
00:14:02,466 --> 00:14:03,467
Hey!

283
00:14:08,013 --> 00:14:13,185
Papa, they're offering
two hundred million.

284
00:14:14,186 --> 00:14:17,064
- [EMIL CHUCKLES]
- But that's not enough.

285
00:14:18,190 --> 00:14:20,025
Ask for more.

286
00:14:20,109 --> 00:14:22,611
Magnus owes us a big one.

287
00:14:22,695 --> 00:14:27,283
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

288
00:14:27,366 --> 00:14:30,953
[PHONE RINGING]

289
00:14:32,580 --> 00:14:33,581
What's the update?

290
00:14:33,998 --> 00:14:35,082
We've got a problem.

291
00:14:35,165 --> 00:14:42,006
[OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

292
00:14:45,634 --> 00:14:46,969
[AREZA] We're following protocol.

293
00:14:47,428 --> 00:14:48,762
But remember,

294
00:14:49,763 --> 00:14:52,683
all the guests at La Playa Roja are VIPs.

295
00:14:52,766 --> 00:14:55,102
We don't know what we're walking into.

296
00:14:55,811 --> 00:14:58,898
Use maximum tolerance when apprehending,

297
00:14:59,481 --> 00:15:01,650
but stay alert at all times.

298
00:15:01,734 --> 00:15:03,277
- Yes, sir!
- Yes, sir!

299
00:15:03,360 --> 00:15:04,320
Let's go, men!

300
00:15:04,403 --> 00:15:05,404
Let's go.

301
00:15:10,409 --> 00:15:13,162
Where are Mommy and Daddy?

302
00:15:13,245 --> 00:15:17,124
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

303
00:15:17,207 --> 00:15:20,169
S-Sir, I have money.

304
00:15:20,252 --> 00:15:21,503
I can pay.

305
00:15:21,587 --> 00:15:23,130
Please believe me.

306
00:15:23,213 --> 00:15:26,467
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

307
00:15:26,967 --> 00:15:29,053
Please have mercy on us.

308
00:15:29,136 --> 00:15:31,055
Have mercy on the child.

309
00:15:31,138 --> 00:15:32,139
[MAN] Quiet!

310
00:15:33,307 --> 00:15:34,308
Move!

311
00:15:35,309 --> 00:15:36,310
Go!

312
00:15:37,895 --> 00:15:42,900
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

313
00:15:47,655 --> 00:15:49,365
I got them in danger, Ma.

314
00:15:53,077 --> 00:15:55,037
Don't blame yourself, dear.

315
00:15:57,915 --> 00:16:01,627
If Olsen were in your situation earlier,

316
00:16:01,710 --> 00:16:03,170
he would've done the same.

317
00:16:05,965 --> 00:16:08,676
He wouldn't let his mother die.

318
00:16:17,601 --> 00:16:19,269
Ma, Pa…

319
00:16:19,353 --> 00:16:24,316
I'm sure they're not going to let us live.

320
00:16:25,275 --> 00:16:27,111
I can negotiate.

321
00:16:27,778 --> 00:16:29,488
They're criminals, Pa.

322
00:16:30,906 --> 00:16:33,200
Negotiation won't work on them.

323
00:16:34,827 --> 00:16:38,789
We need to find a way to escape.

324
00:16:39,206 --> 00:16:42,918
Magnus, why does it seem like he knows us?

325
00:16:45,963 --> 00:16:49,383
I don't understand either.
It's like he knows us well.

326
00:16:52,052 --> 00:16:54,054
- [MAN 1] Move!
- [MAN 2] Hurry!

327
00:16:54,138 --> 00:16:55,431
- [MAN 1] Hurry!
- [MAN 2] Hurry!

328
00:16:56,140 --> 00:16:57,182
I said hurry!

329
00:16:57,725 --> 00:16:59,727
[MAMA ONA PANTING]

330
00:16:59,810 --> 00:17:01,061
- [MAN 2] Hurry!
- [WENDY] Wait!

331
00:17:01,145 --> 00:17:02,312
[MAN 1] Faster!

332
00:17:03,188 --> 00:17:04,481
[MAMA ONA] I'm moving! Wait!

333
00:17:05,399 --> 00:17:07,192
- [MAN 1] Here, here!
- [MAN 2] I said faster!

334
00:17:07,276 --> 00:17:08,902
[OLSEN] Don't touch my mother!

335
00:17:08,986 --> 00:17:10,446
[FIN] Hey, hey, hey!

336
00:17:10,529 --> 00:17:11,989
- [FIN] Sir!
- [MAN 1] Step back!

337
00:17:14,908 --> 00:17:15,909
[MAN 2] What now?

338
00:17:17,995 --> 00:17:19,580
- [WENDY] Have mercy--
- [MAN 1] Quiet!

339
00:17:19,663 --> 00:17:21,582
- Shut up!
- [BLOW LANDS]

340
00:17:21,665 --> 00:17:23,584
[MAN 1] Should I start with this one?

341
00:17:23,667 --> 00:17:25,252
[MAN 2] No, he's on the list.

342
00:17:25,335 --> 00:17:27,337
- Take him! Take him!
- [MAMA ONA CRYING]

343
00:17:27,421 --> 00:17:29,214
- Take him!
- [WENDY] Fin!

344
00:17:29,298 --> 00:17:31,508
[MADDIE] Where are you taking him?

345
00:17:31,592 --> 00:17:32,509
Grandpa, no--

346
00:17:32,593 --> 00:17:33,969
- Hey!
- Step back!

347
00:17:34,053 --> 00:17:37,014
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

348
00:17:37,097 --> 00:17:39,183
- [MAN 1] Take him!
- [MAN 2] Step back!

349
00:17:40,059 --> 00:17:41,935
- That's enough.
- Hey!

350
00:17:42,019 --> 00:17:43,437
Grandpa, no, no!

351
00:17:44,229 --> 00:17:45,814
- [BLOW LANDS]
- [OLSEN GRUNTS]

352
00:17:45,898 --> 00:17:47,566
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

353
00:17:47,649 --> 00:17:50,152
- [MAN 1] Stand up!
- [MAN 2] Stand up!

354
00:17:50,235 --> 00:17:51,862
[MAN 1] Let's finish this!

355
00:17:51,945 --> 00:17:54,031
- Move!
- Move one step!

356
00:17:54,114 --> 00:17:59,745
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

357
00:18:02,706 --> 00:18:04,333
We outnumber them.

358
00:18:07,544 --> 00:18:09,338
We can take them if we work together.

359
00:18:09,421 --> 00:18:12,216
[THRILLING MUSIC PLAYING]

360
00:18:12,299 --> 00:18:14,635
When I shout for help,

361
00:18:14,718 --> 00:18:16,845
remove your blindfolds all at once.

362
00:18:16,929 --> 00:18:19,807
[THRILLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

363
00:18:19,890 --> 00:18:21,475
We'll fight back.

364
00:18:22,768 --> 00:18:27,272
Tell the person next to you
to pass it on quietly.

365
00:18:27,356 --> 00:18:29,191
Go, and be careful.

366
00:18:31,485 --> 00:18:33,403
- Go, hurry.
- Okay.

367
00:18:34,863 --> 00:18:41,829
[THRILLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

368
00:18:55,843 --> 00:19:00,889
[THRILLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

369
00:19:08,230 --> 00:19:10,858
- Help!
- [TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

370
00:19:10,941 --> 00:19:12,276
Help us!

371
00:19:12,359 --> 00:19:13,819
[MIKE] Help!

372
00:19:13,902 --> 00:19:15,279
Help!

373
00:19:15,362 --> 00:19:22,369
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

374
00:19:24,246 --> 00:19:25,873
[MIKE] Help!

375
00:19:25,956 --> 00:19:27,416
Help!

376
00:19:28,876 --> 00:19:29,835
[BLOW LANDS]

377
00:19:31,670 --> 00:19:36,341
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

378
00:19:36,425 --> 00:19:37,926
[MINNIE SOBBING]

379
00:19:39,219 --> 00:19:41,096
[BOBONG] Go on, scream.

380
00:19:42,556 --> 00:19:49,521
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

381
00:19:52,524 --> 00:19:54,026
[GUNSHOTS]

382
00:19:55,110 --> 00:19:55,861
[BODY THUDS]

383
00:19:55,944 --> 00:20:01,283
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

384
00:20:08,749 --> 00:20:10,292
<i>Help me! Don't shoot!</i>

385
00:20:10,375 --> 00:20:11,543
<i>- Olsen!</i>
- [GUNSHOT]

386
00:20:11,627 --> 00:20:13,670
<i>Ma, Ma, Ma!</i>
<i>Don't close your eyes!</i>

387
00:20:13,754 --> 00:20:15,631
[CLAIRE] <i>There's nothing</i>
<i>we can do for your mother.</i>

388
00:20:15,714 --> 00:20:16,924
<i>Then I'll find Dr. Jessie.</i>

389
00:20:17,007 --> 00:20:18,217
<i>I'll come back, I promise.</i>

390
00:20:18,300 --> 00:20:20,594
<i>Welcome to La Playa Roja, sir.</i>

391
00:20:20,677 --> 00:20:24,181
<i>Ben Bonifacio, head of security.</i>
<i>What brings you here?</i>

392
00:20:24,264 --> 00:20:27,392
<i>We received a report</i>
<i>of a hostage situation here.</i>

393
00:20:27,476 --> 00:20:29,978
[DADO]<i> Are you serious, sir?</i>
<i>There's no hostage situation here.</i>

394
00:20:30,062 --> 00:20:32,272
<i>As you can see,</i>
<i>everything's peaceful.</i>

395
00:20:32,356 --> 00:20:33,482
<i>Ma'am, are you okay?</i>

396
00:20:33,565 --> 00:20:37,236
<i>Are you okay waiting tables when you could</i>
<i>be shot if you make a wrong move?</i>

397
00:20:37,319 --> 00:20:39,988
- [LIAM] <i>What do you want from me?</i>
<i>- Take off your clothes. Put that on.</i>

398
00:20:40,072 --> 00:20:42,991
[AREZA] <i>Can we speak to the one</i>
<i>who called our station?</i>

399
00:20:43,075 --> 00:20:44,159
<i>Liam Roja.</i>

400
00:20:44,243 --> 00:20:47,454
[LUNA] <i>Whatever you're</i>
<i>thinking, stop for now.</i>

401
00:20:47,537 --> 00:20:51,166
[LIAM] <i>I can't let anyone else</i>
<i>get hurt because of me.</i>
